e":"January 6, 2025","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/projects/williams-sausage-com/","section":"Projects","summary":"","title":"Williams Sausage Com"},{"content":"","date":"January 6, 2025","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/projects/blackopsanimation/","section":"Projects","summary":"","title":"Blackopsanimation"},{"content":" I saw somewhere this website https://12factor.net, looks interesting let\u0026rsquo;s analyze it.\nInput: #I. One codebase tracked in revision control, many deploys\nII. Explicitly declare and isolate dependencies\nIII. Store config in the environment\nIV. Treat backing services as attached resources\nV. Strictly separate build and run stages\nVI. Execute the app as one or more stateless processes\nVII. Export services via port binding\nVIII. Scale out via the process model\nIX. Maximize robustness with fast startup and graceful shutdown\nX. Keep development, staging, and production as similar as possible\nXI. Treat logs as event streams\nXII. Run admin/management tasks as one-off processes\nAnalysis: # I. One codebase tracked in revision control, many deploys\nbasically trunk based dev, where you have frequent deploys and feature flags. II. Explicitly declare and isolate dependencies\ntrying to pin the versions, keep variance low III. Store config in the environment\nnot sure how to understand it, is it about process environment or dev environment? Assuming process environment (kinda make it possible tweak a program) IV. Treat backing services as attached resources\nmeaning they can be offline / not compatible etc. V. Strictly separate build and run stages\nI think it\u0026rsquo;s already separated for us in mobile dev. VI. Execute the app as one or more stateless processes\ngenerally the less state the better, yes. VII. Export services via port binding\nlooks like something backend. VIII. Scale out via the process model\nsame. IX. Maximize robustness with fast startup and graceful shutdown\nyes :D X. Keep development, staging, and production as similar as possible\ntest on prod, prefer single branch if possible. XI. Treat logs as event streams\nsomething like Sentry, don\u0026rsquo;t expect the results to be available synchronously. XII. Run admin/management tasks as one-off processes\nas I understand basically about limiting the timespan of priviliged code. Takeaways # Version it all: code, pin dependencies, including your dev environment External world is external, not in your control, accept it. Prefer loose coupling Less State - or let\u0026rsquo;s say \u0026ldquo;more computable state\u0026rdquo;. Minimal difference between environments ","date":null,"permalink":"http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/","section":"Notes","summary":"\u003cp\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n    \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \u003cpicture\n      class=\"mx-auto my-0 rounded-md\"\n      \n    \u003e\n      \n      \n      \n      \n        \u003csource\n          \n            srcset=\"http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_eb6ec1f7f518ec45.webp 330w,http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_534d9075877d3f.webp 660w\n            \n              ,http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_d201a3af089d0af7.webp 1024w\n            \n            \n              \n                ,http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_80ecafa584b0ca59.webp 1280w\n              \n            \"\n          \n          sizes=\"100vw\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        /\u003e\n      \n      \u003cimg\n        width=\"1280\"\n        height=\"964\"\n        class=\"mx-auto my-0 rounded-md\"\n        alt=\"feature\"\n        loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"\n        \n          src=\"http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_f099c7b0315b0b0f.jpg\" srcset=\"http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_4d82e9173bb58953.jpg 330w,http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_f099c7b0315b0b0f.jpg 660w\n          \n            ,http://localhost:1313/notes/12-factors/feature_hu_